@mrproliu thanks. So let me summarize:

* queue size `50` with `10ms` dump interval = max `500ms` window size
* and Java Agent drain the queue every `500ms`

Maybe these 2 values are too close, it's a big chance to meet `Queue full`?

Besides, `ProfileTaskChannelService`  use `BlockingQueue.add`:

```java
    public void addProfilingSnapshot(TracingThreadSnapshot snapshot) {
        snapshotQueue.add(snapshot);
    }
```

According to javadoc:

> Inserts the specified element into this queue if it is possible to do so immediately without violating capacity restrictions, returning true upon success and throwing an IllegalStateException if no space is currently available. When using a capacity-restricted queue, it is generally preferable to use offer.

I think use `BlockingQueue.offer` is more appropriate.

More, because of `Queue full` exception thrown, `ProfileThread` will exited prematurely:

```java
ProfileThread.run() {
  ProfileThread.profiling() {
    while(...) {
      ProfileTaskChannelService.addProfilingSnapshot() {
          Queue full exception throws
      }
    }
  }
}
```

